description: Available at: https://openstudionetwork.com/keezer - Good introductions are the key to establishing the tempo, feel and mood of a song. Like "Endings", more often than not it's the pianist's job to create them. This 2-part lesson examines in depth six classic intros from recorded jazz history, and gives you clear and useful guidelines to invent your own. Great for guitarists as well! (Level: Intermediate)
title: Geoffrey Keezer - Intros (Preview)
